import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    restaurant_counts = data['key'].value_counts()
    ax = restaurant_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='tab:blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of restaurant types in the U-District?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Restaurant Types')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Restaurant Types'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['lat'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Latitude')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['lat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude values in the U-District?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['lat'], data['distance'], c=data['key'].cat.codes, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Categories")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Distance')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between latitude and distance in the U-District?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
